● What ECC Does After Installing                                                                                                                                
                                                                            
  Think of it as upgrades to Claude's brain that activate every time you use Claude Code on any project.
                                                                                                                                                                
  ---
  Before ECC                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                  
  Claude Code is smart but generic. You tell it what to do, it figures it out on its own, using one general-purpose Claude instance for everything.

  After ECC

  Claude Code becomes a team of specialists. Instead of one Claude doing everything, it routes tasks to the right expert automatically.

  ---
  The 4 Main Things It Gives You

  1. Specialist Agents (47 of them)

  Instead of one Claude, you get dedicated experts that get called automatically:

  ┌─────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┐
  │       When you ask...       │        ECC calls...        │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ "Review my code"            │ code-reviewer agent        │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ "Plan this feature"         │ planner agent              │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ "My build is broken"        │ build-error-resolver agent │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ "Check for security issues" │ security-reviewer agent    │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ "Review my TypeScript"      │ typescript-reviewer agent  │
  └─────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────┘

  2. Slash Commands (79 of them)

  Pre-built workflows you can trigger instantly:
  - /plan — structured implementation planning
  - /tdd — test-driven development workflow
  - /code-review — full quality review
  - /build-fix — diagnose and fix build errors
  - /e2e — generate end-to-end tests

  3. Skills (180 domain packs)

  Deep knowledge packs that get loaded when relevant — React patterns, Next.js, Django, security hardening, database migrations, Git workflow, etc. Claude stops
   guessing and uses proven patterns.

  4. Automatic Hooks

  Background automations that fire without you asking:
  - Runs Prettier/formatting after every file edit
  - Warns you before pushing to git
  - Scans for console.log left in code
  - Saves a session summary when you stop
  - Runs TypeScript checks after edits

  ---
  The Short Version

  Without ECC: You describe what you want → one Claude figures it out from scratch each time.

  With ECC: Claude has 47 specialists, 180 domain knowledge packs, 79 ready-made workflows, and background automations — all activated automatically based on
  what you're doing.

  It's the difference between hiring a generalist and hiring a full dev team where each person is an expert in their lane.